Specify a temporal duration and the resolution of your data.
An example would be a study that acquires data over a whole
year where data is gathered on a daily basis. You would
select duration = year, resolution = day. Resolution needs
to be smaller or equal duration to make sense!

After the selection click to the plus button to add your
selection. You can specify multiple dates and times if
necessary. Just click on the plus button after each selection
to add the selection to the list.
* For selecting a "point" in time e.g. a day you need to select the start and
end date to meet that needs.
